First Avenue, north from East 94th Street. Prominently shown is a generating plant at 96th - 97th Streets. This is a unit of the Consolidated Edison Company. Note in view 2 the absence of the smoke stack atop same. View 3 is limited to the N. E. corner of East 94th Street. On the right is an eastward view towards the East River.

View 1: August 1933

George L. Balgue

Views 2,3: April 14, 1940

P. L. Sperr
